data: Serving as faculty member since 1992, in Electronics & Communication Department, RVCE, Bangalore-059,
Mechanization of the ringing of Church bell at M/s St. Joseph College Church, Trichy-2 in the year 2000 using ABB DTC drive.
Performance evaluation of reciprocating compressors installed at SSTP, BHEL, Trichy-14.in the year 2004.

Under the center of excellence scheme established calibration facilities for calibration of temperature, pressure, voltage, current and speed. The calibration facilities are established using state of the art instrumentation and traceable to national standards.

subdata.subheading: A New Device to Measure Instantaneous Swept Volume of Reciprocating Machines/Compressors,
data: International Compressor Technology Conference at Purdue University, USA. July 12-15 2004, Pannir Selvam.K, Udyakumar.M, Nageswara Rao.C.

subdata.subheading: In Situ Performance Evaluation of Industrial Reciprocating Air Compressors,
data: In Spanish Journal Frio-Calor-Aire Acondicionado , May 2009. Originally Paper No;1422 in Proc. 19th Itl. Compressor Engineering Conf., Purdue Univ.U.S.A., July 2008, M.Udayakumar, K.Pannirselvam, and T.Suthakar.

Theoretical and Experimental Investigations on Performance Influencing Parameters on Industrial Air Compressors. Project sponsored by MHRD, budget allocation: 6 lakhs. Principal Investigator: Dr.M.Udyakumar, Co-investigator: K.Pannir Selvam.
